item.title: Pasoori Remake Review: Can Arijit Singh Do Justice to Ali Sethi's Classic?
item.description:
If you've been on the internet today, you must have heard that Ali Sethi's Pasoori from Coke Studio has made its way into Bollywood. And yet again like most remakes, the first reactions to the song have been that "it is ruined". But what exactly is it about the song that works or doesn't work? Could Arijit Singh make it better? Or do remakes just not work?

Tune into this episode of Do I Like It to find out.Â

item.title: WR Rankings: Top Performers, Potential Breakouts & Hidden Gems (Ep. 110)
item.description: Join Scott Bogman, Pat Fitzmaurice, and Alfredo Brown (@ThePretendGM) from Footballguys as they dissect the top 36 consensus dynasty WR rankings and discuss how their personal rankings compare. From Justin Jefferson to John Metchie III, they lay out comprehensive analysis of the elites, the breakouts, the sleepers, and the busts to help you construct a winning team. What pushes Jaxon Smith-Njigba near WR1 territory as a rookie? The Pros will tell you!
